body:
I'm using Verilator under windows 10. I'm using SystemC. My SystemC project is used through a dll (Visual Studio 2017). I've some exported function in the dll. Without verilator everything is good. I can also compile the verilated source in MSVC. When I change my main.cpp file to this the dll still compiles but I have *no exported* function 'Creating library' message missing also in the build log. What may the problem?

```C
#include "Vcounter.h"

int sc_main(int argc, char* argv[]) {
  Verilated::commandArgs(argc, argv);
  Vcounter* top = new Vcounter("TOP");
  return 0;
}
```

